The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Lanka Ravi best

Ahmedabad: International Master Lanka Ravi of Petroleum Sports Promotion Board won his maiden National B chess title after signing peace with Vikramaditya Kamble of Maharashtra in the 13th and final round on Sunday. 

Ravi, who had raced to 6.5 out of a possible 7 points in the first half of the tournament, scored a crucial victory over Valay Parikh in the ninth round and thereafter four quick draws were enough to fetch him the title. Himanshu Sharma of Haryana finished a creditable second after drawing his last round with G. Rohit of Andhra Pradesh. 

While Ravi finished the championship with 10 points out of a possible 13, Himanshu managed 9.5. 

Thereafter, there was a tie involving 27 players which required a tie-break and Suvrajit Saha of Bengal, emerged on top. 

